# agents.map — the single place that declares your agents.
#
# In the original system this mapping was hardcoded across ~6 scripts
# (wire-skills, cron-postmortem-watch, promote-queue-status, ...). The harness
# reads it from here instead, so adding/renaming an agent is a one-file edit.
#
# Format (one agent per line):  <agent-id>  <workspace-dir>  <persona-label>
#   agent-id      : short id used by the gateway + scripts (e.g. main, dev)
#   workspace-dir : path under ${OPENCLAW_HOME}, e.g. workspace or workspace-dev
#   persona-label : human display name (free choice)
#
# The two-agent default below is the minimal working set. Add rows to grow.

main   workspace       Orchestrator
dev    workspace-dev   Developer

# Examples you might add (uncomment + rename to taste):
# research   workspace-research   Researcher
# ops        workspace-ops        Operator
